{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03446/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03446"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:34:46"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman sitting in an armchair by a fire speaks to someone offscreen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03446","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03446"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1/fa62e3aa-6df5-43bc-8d88-1cefb2654351","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T15:15:54.152Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Alma asserts her ability to stand longer than anyone else (in essence suggesting that she is the perfect fit for Reynolds’s demanding nature), PTA returns to the fireside chat. Her confession’s strongest proclamations demand that she be present in the frame. The audience still doesn’t know to whom she’s speaking, though. PTA saw a similar energy in actress Vicky Krieps: “God, she’s so strong, that Vicky. And she had to take it, a lot. The dynamics of that relationship meant that there were days and days of standing and being on the back foot and dutifully keeping her mouth shut” (Buchanan, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW51905023 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2017/12/director-paul-thomas-anderson-on-phantom-thread-mortality.html\"><u>Love, Death, and Control</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:633.1090174966353,238.30417227456263,722.2611036339165,547.8331090174966"}}}]},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03446/canvas/1/page/p2","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[]}]}]}